@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<hgroup class="title">
    <h1>@ViewBag.Title.</h1>
    <h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
</hgroup>

<article>
    <p>
        This is just  a Demo project. It's not a big deal but I hope it help me to show how
        a project can be deployed using Azure.
    </p>

    <p>
        I show you some design patterns to illustrate how can be implemented
        using dot NET platform.
    </p>

    <p>
        Some features I used on this projects were:
    </p>

    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>Asp net MVC and Telerik for the UI</li>
            <li>Fluent API for validations</li>
            <li>
                Entity Framework
                <ul>
                    <li>It was implemented using Repository design Pattern. It allow us to create diferent repositories according the different storing </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>C#</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
</article>

<aside>
    <h3>Telerik UI for ASP.NET MVC TreeView</h3>
    <p>
        Use this area to provide additional information.
    </p>

    @(Html.Kendo().TreeView()
        .Name("LinksTreeView")
        .Items(items =>
        {
            items.Add()
                .Text("Home")
                .Action("Index", "Home");
            items.Add()
                .Text("About")
                .Action("About", "Home");
            items.Add()
                .Text("Contact")
                .Action("Contact", "Home");
        })
    )

</aside>
